article.headline: Long Beach State 74, Manhattan 61
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon scored 15 points to lead Long Beach State to a 74-61 victory over Manhattan Saturday. With the scored tied 41-41 with 15:56 remaining in the game, Nixon led a 13-2 run giving the 49'ers a 54-43 lead. The Jaspers never got any closer than six points the rest of the way. The 49'ers (9-4) have won seven straight games and improved to 4-0 at home. Manhattan (3-8) lost their third straight game and have dropped seven of eight and fell to 1-4 on the road. Kejuan Johnson scored 13 points and Kevin Houston and Louis Darby added 11 a piece for Long Beach State who went 7-1 in December. Devon Austin led the Jaspers with 14 points and Darryl Crawford added 11. The Jaspers shot only 328 percent (21-64) for the game. The 49'ers shot 57.9 (11-19) in the second-half. Manhattan started the game with a 10-0 run. Long Beach State countered with a 14-1 rally to take the lead. Manhattan out-rebounded the 49'ers 22-15 in the first-half. The Jaspers made 13-of-30 shots (43.3 percent) in the opening half while Long Beach State shot 34.5 percent (10 for 29).
